_prev_prog_3.Description:
The propylene unloading rail station and storage tank comply with OSHA Standard 29 CFR 1910.119, Process Safety Management of highly hazardous chemicals, and FHR has applied the programs and policies found in the standard to activities throughout the facility. Specific program elements include: 

(i)    Employee Participation ? It is the policy of Flint Hills Resources (FHR) to seek participation of employees at all levels in establishing procedures and practices that govern Health, Safety and Environmental issues. The PSM Manual includes a description of how the Employee Participation element is implemented in Section 4.0;

(ii)    Process Safety Information ? Process safety information is maintained for the facility. The PSM Manual includes a description of how the Process Safety Information element is implemented in Section 5.0; 

(iii)    Process Hazard Analysis ? A detailed process hazard assessment, using HAZOP, is conducted on the facility to ensure that it has been designed safely. The PSM Manual includes a description of how the Process Hazard Analysis element is implemented in Section 6.0; 

(iv)    Operating Procedures ? A system is in place to ensure that updated and approved procedures cover all aspects of the facility's operation. The PSM Manual includes a description of how the Operating Procedure element is implemented in Section 7.0;

(v)    Training ? A training program has been established to ensure that all personnel are well trained in the specific duties of their jobs (The process also includes an annual Training Needs Analysis). The PSM Manual includes a description of how the Training element is implemented in Section 8.0;

(vi)    Contractors ? It is FHR's objective to partner with contractors that share the same safety philosophy. A dedicated, collective, and consistent approach by FHR and contractors will enhance and maintain the safety and health of our respective employees. The PSM Contractor Management Program element is included in Section 9.0 of the PSM Manual; 

(vii)    Prestartup Safety Review ? A pre-startup safety review walk down and checklist is completed for each managed change that significantly impacts the Process Safety Information. The PSM Manual includes a description of how the Pre-startup Safety Review element is implemented in Section 10.0; 

(viii)    Mechanical Integrity ? An equipment inspection program is in place to ensure equipment remains in good condition to prevent releases. The PSM Manual includes a description of how the Mechanical Integrity element is implemented in Section 11.0; 

(ix)    Hot Work Permits ? A work permit system is in place to ensure that all work on process equipment and all hot work are conducted in a safe manner. The PSM Manual and includes a description of how the Hot Work element is implemented in Section 12.0. Site procedure MOLPU-004 covers hot work permitting at the rail facility;

(x)    Management of Change ? A management of change system has been established and implemented to ensure that any change is thoroughly reviewed prior to implementation. The PSM Manual includes a description of how the Management of Change element is implemented in Section 13.0; 

(xi)    Incident Investigation ? Incidents are investigated using one of several industry recognized methodologies, such as Tap Root to determine system level root causes that can be remedied to prevent a recurrence. Employees and contractors involved in the incident are included on the investigation team. The PSM Manual includes a description of how the Incident Investigation element is implemented in Section 14.0; 

(xii)    Emergency Planning and Response ? An emergency action plan has been established, and the site is part of the Community Emergency Response Plan. The PSM Manual includes a description of how the Emergency Planning and Response element is implemented in Section 15.0; 

(xiii)    Compliance Audits ? Programs are audited annually; at least every three years through PSM compliance audits; and weekly safety inspections of the facility are conducted by cross functional teams. Action items resulting from these are tracked to a timely completion. The PSM Manual includes a description of how the Compliance Audit element is implemented in Section 16.0;

(xiv)    Trade Secrets ? There are no Trade Secret issues at the facility.
